<br>
Measuring FPs in pounds is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>completely</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> misleading.  Radioactivity, and particularly biological effeectiveness, is the only relevant characteristic.<br>
<br>
Do you know what a horrifying quantity of radioactivity is contained in 10 pounds of fresh fission products from a reator at equilibrium??<br>
<br>
Its like saying that all the botulism toxin in all the spoiled food in the world would not fill a tablespoon. So what? That is enough to kill much of the world's population.<br>
<br>
An equitorial failed orbit of that rocket stands a real chance of dispersing it gaseous FPs over the densest population zones on earth.<br>
